A pretty exciting night, this last one was. As I was sitting on my porch having a smoke and reading the news ( much as I always do) this guy walks by whom Id shared a CS class with last semester.  We'ed always given the 'whats up' to each other, cause, well, thats what smokers do.  We got talking and he invited me to this party, and it was the wierdest goddamn thing Id ever seen.  Most of the time we just drank beer and watched South Park and shit, but then this guy started running around with a slingshot and bb gun.  That was interesting.  To escape the projectiles, me and a few guys went upstairs to these girls' apartment and sat around talking about geo-politca bullshit.  I think I totally impressed them with my "Why George Bush should be re-elected" speech.  You know, the funny one about armageddon and what have you.  Then me and this girl named Autumn drank tea and smoked on her balcony for what must have been an hour just talking about all the cool shit we knew (obviously, most of it was from classes).  She's a Literary Studies major so we had alot to talk about, considering Ive taken at least one Lit. class every semester since Ive been in college.  Then I noticed all the guys had gone downstairs, so I ent down and found out that a bottle of vody got cracked and then began the confusion.  I think I came back home around 4 or so.

So I'm in my apartment after GOVT 2301 and listening to Ayu full blast.  Although I was really homesick the first night, I seem to feel for comfortable here than in Odessa.  Probably because I have pillows and my elephant lamp.  My roommates are never here, so its usually pretty lonely.  I went home this past weekend I did exactly what I always did, sit around Sean's, drink, smoke pot, and play Hawk.  Its funny that this campus is full of people that share my interests.  Everyone plays Tekken, Smash, and Dance Dance.  Somehow, even with all the atheists, intellectuals, and anime nerds, I still feel out of place.  I'm lucky that I grew up in Odessa, for it makes me quite the individual.  Spencer let me have/borrow his skateboard, so getting to class is hella easy.  Downhill both ways.  I know this makes me the lowest of the low; the cursed transport skater, but hey, one must do what it takes.  I do miss everyone back home though and I'm sad that I will only be able to see Marta one last time.
